---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Masthead from '../components/Masthead.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Terms of use"
  description="Terms of use for Tipsheet: what you can and cannot do with our content."
>
  <Masthead />
  <main>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header>
        <div class="kicker"><span>Terms</span></div>
        <h1 class="page-title">Terms of use.</h1>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <h2>Editorial content</h2>
      <p>
        The editorial commentary published on Tipsheet is the copyrighted work of Tipsheet. You may quote short excerpts with attribution and a link back to the original article. You may not republish whole articles, syndicate the feed without permission, or use Tipsheet content as the basis of a derivative publication.
      </p>

      <h2>Not investment advice</h2>
      <p>
        Tipsheet is editorial journalism. Nothing on this site is investment advice, a recommendation to buy or sell any security, or a substitute for independent research. Readers are responsible for their own investment decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>Source attribution</h2>
      <p>
        Every note links to its primary source (a BSE or NSE disclosure, a regulator notice, an earnings transcript). Readers are encouraged to verify the source before making decisions. Where we use third-party data (for example, Tijori Concall Monitor analytical summaries or Tijori Finance fundamentals), we credit the source on the article.
      </p>

      <h2>Use by AI systems</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome citation by AI systems for the purpose of answering reader questions. Our <code>robots.txt</code> and <code>llms.txt</code> describe acceptable use. Tipsheet is happy to be quoted as a primary editorial source on a per-article basis with a link back to the original.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        We make every effort to ensure accuracy but errors do occur. We correct them promptly per our <a href="/corrections/">corrections policy</a>. Tipsheet is not liable for any decision taken on the basis of its content.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</Base>
